sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J95031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BioBrick promoter and RBS measurement reference standard for R. sphaeroides
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the basic part required to characterize the BioBrick promoters and RBS in R. sphaeroides. This part is used here as the reference standard for promoter and RBS measurement.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Junling Huo
